      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil, </strong>once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>then cook over a medium heat for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Add your <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy), <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>lean pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!)</p><p>Season with<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 5-7 min until crispy and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
